Program: The History Hour
Title: The Russian Revolution: The Bolsheviks Take Control
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/w3csvstw
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 12 Nov 2017
Eye-witness accounts from the Russian Revolution of October 1917; the first dog in space; Sabah, one of the biggest 20th-century stars of the Middle East; the last journalist to interview Osama Bin Laden; and horror and heartbreak: memories of the First World War. Picture: Bolshevik leader Vladimir Lenin addressing crowds in the capital Petrograd during the Russian Revolution of 1917. (Credit: Hulton Archive/Getty Images) Show less